A part program has been stopped. Causes may be a malfunction that has occurred, or an intervention of the operator. This signal is aggregated from ?StoppedOperator? and ?StoppedMalfunction?. In this condition resuming the program is possible after acknowledging the feedhold or the malfunction.
The program has been stopped by a malfunction, for example a machine fault that prevents it from cycling.
A program or machine cycle has been stopped by the operator ( ). This can be done by either pressing feedhold or by interrupting a lightbarrier or by setting the FeedrateOverride to 0%.
